;; EXPECT: panic
;; AC_COMPLETE: on
;; Regression guard for the nested-same-op / flattening blocker (design §6b "Hard
;; prerequisite"). With AC completion ON and NO flattening, completion superposes the
;; two overlapping sums add(a,b), add(b,c) and materializes a nested node add(add..,..).
;; The matcher assumes flat AC terms (WF_flat): decomposing the nested node reaches an
;; unbound plan variable and panics. This is the documented reason completion is gated
;; off by default until flattening lands; this test PINS that it still panics, so when
;; flattening is implemented this test flips (EXPECT: ok) and proves the fix.
;;
;; Reproduced through the real driver under both naive and semi-naive (check_panic runs
;; both), confirming it is a genuine matcher precondition, not a stale white-box test.

(sort E)
(function f (E E) E)
(function g (E) E)
(function add (E) E :assoc-comm)
(function a () E)
(function b () E)
(function c () E)

;; Two same-op AC atoms with rest variables, the shape that exercises the nested node.
(rewrite (f (add x ..r1) (add y ..r2)) (g x))

;; The overlapping-sums graph that drives completion's superposition.
(let t (f (add (a) (b)) (add (b) (c))))

(run 10)
